-- Philip Brook Is Appointed New Chairman of All England Lawn Tennis Club
-- B y   D a n i e l l e   R o s s i n g h
-- 2010-12-09T12:38:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-09/philip-brook-appointed-new-chairman-of-all-england-lawn-tennis-club.html
The All England Lawn Tennis Club,
which hosts the  Wimbledon Championships , appointed  Philip Brook 
as its new chairman.  Brook, previously the club’s vice chairman, replaces  Tim Phillips , who’s retired after 11 years, the club said in an
e-mailed statement today.  Brook, 54, is a former captain of the tennis team at
Cambridge University, where he studied mathematics. He’s also a
former partner at consultant Towers Watson and retired from the
company after 18 years in 2009.  The Wimbledon Championships will be held June 20 through
July 3 next year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
